    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const redis = require('redis');\nconst item = $input.first().json;\nif (!item.file_hash) {\n  return [{ json: item }];\n}\nlet redisPw = ''; try { redisPw = $env.REDIS_PASSWORD || ''; } catch(e) {}\nconst client = redis.createClient({ socket: { host: 'redis', port: 6379 }, password: redisPw || undefined });\nawait client.connect();\ntry {\n  // BUG-2 fix: remove stale old hash from queued_files on Fall 3 replace\n  if (item._lifecycle_action === 'replace' && item._old_hash) {\n    await client.sRem('alice:dms:queued_files', item._old_hash);\n  }\n  await client.sAdd('alice:dms:queued_files', item.file_hash);\n} finally {\n  await client.quit();\n}\nreturn [{ json: item }];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        36816,
        3888
      ],
      "id": "code-mark-queued-01-alice-dms-scanner-v1",
      "name": "Code: Mark Queued"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Summary Stats: aggregate counters from all loop iterations\nconst allItems = $('Code: Lifecycle Check').all();\nconst hashItems = $('Code: Hash + Size').all();\nconst folders = $('PG: Active Folders').all();\n\nconst scannedDirs = folders.length;\nconst scannedFiles = hashItems.length;\n\nlet newFiles = 0;\nlet skippedFiles = 0;\nconst errors = [];\n\nfor (const item of allItems) {\n  const action = item.json._lifecycle_action;\n  if (action === 'already_processed' || action === 'already_queued') {\n    skippedFiles++;\n  } else if (action === 'new' || action === 'replace' || action === 'update_path' || action === 'add_path') {\n    newFiles++;\n  } else if (item.json._skip) {\n    skippedFiles++;\n  }\n}\n\n// Count hash errors\nfor (const item of hashItems) {\n  if (item.json._skip && item.json._skip_reason) {\n    skippedFiles++;\n    errors.push(item.json._skip_reason);\n  }\n}\n\n// Runtime: estimate from execution start to now\nlet runtimeSeconds = 0;\ntry {\n  const startMs = new Date($execution.startedAt).getTime();\n  runtimeSeconds = Math.round((Date.now() - startMs) / 1000);\n} catch(e) { runtimeSeconds = 0; }\n\nconsole.log(`Summary: dirs=${scannedDirs} files=${scannedFiles} new=${newFiles} skipped=${skippedFiles} errors=${errors.length} runtime=${runtimeSeconds}s`);\nreturn [{ json: { scanned_dirs: scannedDirs, scanned_files: scannedFiles, new_files: newFiles, skipped_files: skippedFiles, errors: errors, runtime_seconds: runtimeSeconds } }];"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        37104,
        3888
      ],
      "id": "summary-stats-01-alice-dms-scanner-v1",
      "name": "Code: Summary Stats"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## alice-dms-scanner\n\nScheduled hourly (07:00-22:00).\n\nScans NAS folders from alice.dms_watched_folders,\nfinds new documents, checks lifecycle via redis,\nverifies file stability (5s wait),\nchecks PDF text layer for OCR needs,\nroutes to type-specific MQTT queues:\n- alice/dms/pdf (PDF with text layer)\n- alice/dms/ocr (PDF needing OCR)\n- alice/dms/txt (TXT, MD)\n- alice/dms/office (DOCX, DOC, ODT, XLSX, XLS, ODS)\n\n### Redis Key Pattern (PROJ-21)\n- `alice:dms:processed` — Set of processed file hashes\n- `alice:dms:queued_files` — Set of in-flight file hashes\n- `alice:dms:path_to_hash` — Hash map: file_path -> file_hash\n- `alice:dms:hash_to_paths:<hash>` — Set of known paths per hash\n\n### Lifecycle Detection (PROJ-21)\nUses redis Code nodes for Set/Hash operations.\nDetects: new files, duplicates (add_path),\nmoved files (update_path), changed files (replace).\nPublishes lifecycle events to alice/dms/lifecycle.",
        "height": 440,
